            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.16.18"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">18</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <unclear>715</unclear> <unclear/> Street
                        Muskogee, Oklahoma
                        January 25, 1934
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr Niehardt<sic>Neihardt</sic></salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am a member of the Muskogee Junior College. In our course of study we have taken up the epic.</p>
                
                <p>I chose your Song of the Indian Wars as the subject of my talk. My instructor Miss Bessie <unclear>Huff</unclear> maintains that your work is not an epic. I have <unclear/> convinced her that your <unclear>poem</unclear> <unclear/> all of the qualifications of an epic, but now she holds that it is not old enough to have proved itself yet and that only time can prove that it is an epic.</p>
                    
                <p>She granted me this <unclear>resort</unclear> however &#8212; if I can prove that it has the qualities which will make it endure the ravages of time she will be convinced. I am very anxious to do this for I have become very <unclear>interested in</unclear> the "Song of the Indian Wars" and feel, as you do, that it is the Great American Epic. I enjoyed reading it "very" much</p>
                    
                <p>I have written to you with the hope that you can help me. You, of course know much more about it than anyone else, <unclear/> the <unclear/> All you could tell me of the epic would be deeply appreciated.</p>
                    
                <p>Owing to the short time allowed for the assignment I hope you can find time to answer my letter soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Viola Gard</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>715 <unclear>Fredonia</unclear> Street</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Muskogee Oklahoma</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
